# ARVES — CODEOWNERS
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: mark the FROZEN trees so that any pull request touching them REQUIRES
# review from the freeze owners. This is the human half of the freeze gate; the
# mechanical half is `verification/freeze/freeze_check.py check` (wired into
# .github/workflows/ci.yml), which fails CI on ANY drift of a frozen file.
#
# The freeze is defined by the ARVES Engineering Constitution (CLAUDE.md) and the
# Runtime Freeze Record (runtime/RUNTIME_FREEZE_v1.0.md):
#   * runtime/  — Runtime v1.0, byte-stable; changes ONLY via a Runtime Change
#                 Request (RCR).
#   * standard/ — the frozen Standard; changes ONLY via a CCP Amendment / IDR.
# No product-side or ad-hoc edit may land in either tree.
#
# NOTE ON ENFORCEMENT: CODEOWNERS only *requests/*requires review when the repo
# has branch protection with "Require review from Code Owners" enabled on the
# GitHub host. No CI host is wired yet (this repo has no remote), so this file is
# the review-gate DEFINITION; branch protection must be turned on when the repo
# is hosted. The freeze_check.py gate in ci.yml is host-independent and is the
# authoritative mechanical stop.
#
# Owners are placeholder maintainer groups; replace with real GitHub teams/handles
# when the repo is hosted (e.g. @arves/runtime-team, @arves/standard-team).
# =============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FROZEN — Runtime v1.0. Runtime Team owns; changes only via RCR.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/runtime/                       @arves-maintainers @arves-runtime-team

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FROZEN — the Standard. Standard Team owns; changes only via CCP Amendment/IDR.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/standard/                      @arves-maintainers @arves-standard-team

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The freeze machinery itself (the gate that guards the two trees above) and its
# rolling baseline manifest. Changing the gate or its baseline must be reviewed
# by the maintainers, because a silent manifest edit could hide real drift.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/verification/freeze/           @arves-maintainers

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI + freeze/review configuration (this lane). Maintainer review.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/                       @arves-maintainers
/Dockerfile                     @arves-maintainers
